---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Beta" description="Run one chat interface for AI CLIs across your own devices.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="surface">
      <div class="eyebrow">Developer Control Plane</div>
      <h1>One chat surface for all your AI CLI tools.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        BridgeAIChat connects Codex, Claude, and other CLI-native tools running on your laptop, desktop, VPS, or
        Raspberry Pi behind a single web UI. Your gateway, your agents, your devices — Tailscale handles the private
        networking.
      </p>
      <div class="pill-row">
        <span class="pill">Tailnet login beta</span>
        <span class="pill">GitHub release install</span>
        <span class="pill">Self-hosted control plane</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="button primary" href="/downloads">Install the beta</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/docs/quickstart">Read the quickstart</a>
      </div>
      <div class="metric-grid">
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>1 UI</strong>
          <span>laptop, VPS, and edge boxes together</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>0 hosted runtime</strong>
          <span>nothing runs in our cloud</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>3 device states</strong>
          <span>Connected, Agent Missing, Offline</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:0.75rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">bridge-gateway</span>
      </div>
      <pre><span style="color:#6b9f6b"># set Tailscale API credentials</span>
export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_ID=tsid_xxx
export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_SECRET=tssecret_xxx
export TAILSCALE_API_BASE=https://api.tailscale.com/api/v2
export APP_URL=http://localhost:8080

<span style="color:#e8a87c">./bridge-gateway</span>
<span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35)">→ listening on :8080</span>

<span style="color:#6b9f6b"># open in browser, enter your tailnet</span>
<span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35)">http://localhost:8080</span>
<span style="color:#e8a87c">example.ts.net</span>

<span style="color:#6b9f6b"># on each agent device</span>
export BRIDGE_AGENT_GATEWAY_URL=ws://host:8080/agent
<span style="color:#e8a87c">bash install-agent.sh</span></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid three">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Own the Runtime</div>
      <h2>Execution stays where your tools already live.</h2>
      <p>BridgeAIChat wraps your local CLI tools with a shared control surface. Nothing is rerouted through an external server — every command runs on the device it's configured for.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Fleet Visibility</div>
      <h2>See which machine is reachable, at a glance.</h2>
      <p>The UI merges Tailscale device status with live Bridge agent connections, so you always know whether a machine is ready, missing an agent, or fully offline.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Beta Shape</div>
      <h2>Minimal login, no hosted auth required.</h2>
      <p>The beta uses a tailnet input form in place of Tailscale OAuth. Enter your tailnet name and the gateway calls the Tailscale API directly with your credentials.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">How it works</div>
      <h2>Three components, clear responsibilities.</h2>
      <div class="arch-item">
        <span class="arch-tag">bridge-ai-app</span>
        <p>Runs the gateway process, serves the web UI, and queries the Tailscale API to discover and track your devices.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-item">
        <span class="arch-tag">bridge-ai-agent</span>
        <p>Runs on each remote machine. Maintains a WebSocket back to the gateway and spawns your local AI CLI tool on demand.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-item">
        <span class="arch-tag">bridge-ai-docs</span>
        <p>This site — install guides, tool configuration reference, and troubleshooting for the current beta.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Best fit</div>
      <h2>Who should try the beta.</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Developers running Codex or Claude CLI across more than one machine</li>
        <li>Homelab operators with GPU boxes, VPS hosts, or Raspberry Pi nodes</li>
        <li>Platform engineers who want a private, inspectable AI execution path</li>
        <li>Early testers comfortable running a gateway with local Tailscale credentials</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .arch-item {
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .arch-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SFMono-Regular', Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--teal);
    background: var(--teal-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--teal-soft-border);
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .arch-item p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .terminal pre {
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #d4d0ca;
  }
</style>
